subject: Implements PowerSubsystem and PowerSupply schema
commitMessage:
Implements PowerSubsystem and PowerSupply schema

The PowerSubsystem, PowerSupply, PowerSupplyMetrics, and
EnvironmentMetrics schemas  were added in 2020.4 as a replacement
for the Power schema. This commit implements the root of the new
"Power" model, the  PowerSubsystem. From the PowerSubsystem all
other Power schemas can be reached.

An implementation can support both the new Power schemas
and the old and OpenBMC should do the same for the time being.

Also some info out at
https://www.dmtf.org/sites/default/files/standards/documents/DSP-IS0015_v0.9a.zip
from when these were proposed

This commit implements Redfish PowerSubsystem and PowerSupply schema
on bmcweb. The PowerSupply schema is a power supply for a Redfish
implementation. It is used to get the power supply information of
the chassis, such as PartNumber, SerialNumber, Model and so on.

ref: https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/PowerSupply.v1_0_0.json

This function uses associations to determine whether the PowerSupply
belongs to the chassis. We need to add a chassis association to the
PowerSupply, for example:
https://gist.github.com/ChicagoDuan/7cfdf17466257596c97566a78cbfc6f1

Tested: Validator passes
